#Text=Change the Engine Air Filter on a WK2 Jeep Grand Cherokee
#Text=Maintenance is arguably the most important path to ensuring vehicle longevity .

#Text=Following the owner 's manual maintenance schedule is critical to keeping your vehicle in good condition . Changing the engine air filter on your own can help ensure that the job is done correctly , and will allow you to avoid being overcharged by crooked maintenance shops .
#Text=The following steps will show you how to change the engine air filter on a WK2 Jeep Grand Cherokee .
#Text=Steps
#Text=Get an air filter .
#Text=Although there is always a lot of controversy on what brand should be purchased , getting an OEM ( original equipment manufacturer ) will always be your best bet .
#Text=It is what was tested in your vehicle for optimal efficiency and longevity , and it will not void your warranty if something goes wrong with your air flow system .
#Text=Locate the hood release switch .
#Text=This switch is located below the " gas cap " release button and has a picture of a car with the hood open .

column1: #Text=Once found , pull on the switch to release the " safety " latch .
#Text=Unlatch the hood .
#Text=Go directly in front , and to the middle of the vehicle .
#Text=Place hand underneath the hood and locate the latch .
#Text=Once located , unlatch it and the hood should open up by itself .
#Text=Locate the air box .
#Text=The air box is the first stage in which air goes through to get to the engine .
#Text=It is usually connected to a longer , cylindrical tube .
#Text=In this Jeep 's case , it is behind the drivers side headlight .
#Text=Locate the fasteners .
#Text=There are 2 fasteners holding the air box in place .
#Text=Both are located on the same side .
#Text=One is under the power steering reservoir .
#Text=Release the clip fasteners from place .
#Text=This is done by simply pushing the fasteners away from the air box .
#Text=Once off the air box , The clips will stand in place , so there is no worry about losing them .
#Text=Open up the air box .
#Text=Grab the edge opposite of the black tube , and lift .
#Text=Remove the air filter .
#Text=Grab on to any side of the filter and take it out .
#Text=These filters are quite flexible , so do n't worry about how you handle them .
#Text=Inspect your filter .
#Text=According to the owners manual in all WK2 Jeep Grand Cherokee 's , these filters should be replaced every .
#Text=But If the engine is under constant heavy loads , like when towing , or driving in dusty areas , these filters might need replacing more often .
#Text=Take a look and see how the condition of your filter is , and replace it accordingly .
#Text=Place new filter in .
#Text=It is very important that you pay attention to the " air flow " directional arrow .
#Text=This will let you know how to place in the filter .
#Text=Luckily , these filters are only designed to fit in one way , with the fenced off metal portion facing the hood .
#Text=So there is no way of messing up this step !
#Text=Secure air box back into place .
#Text=Place the air box back into the original position .
#Text=Once back into the original position , secure the clips back on to the air box .
#Text=Close the hood .
#Text=After disposing of the old air filter and closing the hood , you 're good to go back on the road !
#Text=Tips
#Text=Wear gloves to help keep dirt from underneath your nails and to help protect your hands from minor cuts or scratches .
#Text=Warnings
#Text=Do NOT change your air filter while the car is on .
#Text=Opening up the air box while the car is on will not allow air flow to travel to the engine .
#Text=This will cause your engine to run rich ( to much fuel to air mixture ) , and leave unburned fuel in the exhaust system , which could cause carbon build up .
